# ModNN

**ModNN** is a Modularized Physics-Informed Neural Network for building energy modeling.
It incorporates with physics-informed model structure, loss function, and model constraints.

---

## 🚀 Installation

You can install the package using pip:
pip install ModNN
Or install locally by git clone


## 🧠 Example Usage
Please check the example file

Call print_help() for a list of available arguments:
from ModNN.config import print_help
print_help()

🧪 Requirements

    Python 3.7+

    PyTorch

    NumPy

    Pandas

    Matplotlib

    Seaborn

    scikit-learn

    tqdm

Install requirements with:

pip install -r requirements.txt

📁 Folder Structure

ModNN/
├── Config.py
├── Dataset.py
├── utils.py
├── Play.py
├── run.py
├── Models/
│   ├── ModNN.py
│   └── BaseNN.py
Examples/
├── Example.py

📊 Input Data Format

The model expects a time-indexed CSV file with the following columns:
Column Name	Description	Example Values
temp_room	Measured room/zone temperature [°F]	72.1, 73.4
temp_amb	Ambient/outdoor air temperature [°F]	80.5, 79.2
solar	Solar radiation [W/m²]	120.5, 340.1
occ	Occupancy schedule (0–1 or number of occupants)	0, 1, 0.5
phvac	HVAC power input (heating/cooling) [W]	-3000, 0, 2000

Additionally:

    The index of the CSV must be a datetime format like "MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM" or "YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS".

    day_sin and day_cos (time-of-day sinusoidal features) will be added automatically by the system.

    All features are automatically scaled using MinMaxScaler to the range [-1, 1], and for phvac, you can use a custom scale if you want.

